# QA audit HIGH finding (H-02): "Zero security headers on frontend"
#
# This file has NO EFFECT on plain GitHub Pages — GH Pages serves files as-is
# and does not support custom response headers, full stop. It's included so
# these headers take effect automatically, with no backend changes, the
# moment this site is either:
#   (a) fronted by Cloudflare (free tier — Transform Rules / a Worker can
#       apply these to the GitHub Pages origin), or
#   (b) moved to a host that reads this file natively: Netlify, Cloudflare
#       Pages, or Vercel (as vercel.json headers) all support the same
#       "_headers" convention.
#
# The <meta> tags added to each page's <head> (Content-Security-Policy,
# Referrer-Policy) work today on GitHub Pages as a partial mitigation — but
# X-Frame-Options, Strict-Transport-Security, X-Content-Type-Options, and
# CSP's frame-ancestors directive are only meaningful as real HTTP headers,
# which is what this file provides once hosting supports it.

/*
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https://www.googletagmanager.com https://cdn.jsdelivr.net; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https://fonts.googleapis.com; font-src https://fonts.gstatic.com; img-src 'self' data: https:; media-src 'self' https://ttsand-stt.onrender.com https://rairwoyaesgvezxyztnq.supabase.co; connect-src 'self' https://maitrilearn-backend-rag.onrender.com https://ttsand-stt.onrender.com https://rairwoyaesgvezxyztnq.supabase.co https://*.google-analytics.com https://*.analytics.google.com; frame-ancestors 'none'; object-src 'none'; base-uri 'self'; form-action 'self'
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=63072000; includeSubDomains; preload
